# <type>: <short summary, 50 chars or less, imperative mood>
# |----->|----------------------------------------------------|

# Why is this change needed? What problem does it solve?
# (wrap body text at ~72 chars)

# How does it address the issue? Any notable implementation details?

# Any side effects, breaking changes, or things reviewers should watch for?

# Refs: #issue-number
# Co-authored-by: Name <email>

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   refactor (no functional change)
#   docs     (documentation only)
#   style    (formatting, no code change)
#   test     (adding/updating tests)
#   chore    (build, tooling, dependencies)
# --------------------
# Remember to:
#   - Use imperative mood ("Add" not "Added" or "Adds")
#   - Capitalize the summary line
#   - No period at the end of the summary line
#   - Separate summary from body with a blank line
